com.linecorp.armeria.client.metric

Class DropwizardMetricCollectingClient<I extends Request,O extends Response>

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Client<I,O>

    public final class DropwizardMetricCollectingClient<I extends Request,O extends Response>
extends SimpleDecoratingClient<I,O>
    Decorates a Client to collect metrics into Dropwizard MetricRegistry. To use, simply prepare a MetricRegistry and add this decorator to a client.

    Example: 

    
 MetricRegistry metricRegistry = new MetricRegistry();
 MyService.Iface client = new ClientBuilder(uri)
         .decorate(DropwizardMetricCollectingClient.newDecorator(
                 metricRegistry, MetricRegistry.name("clients", "myService")))
         .build(MyService.Iface.class);

    It is generally recommended to define your own name for the service instead of using something like the Java class to make sure otherwise safe changes like renames don't break metrics.
